        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 28 at 9:17PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>At 916 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Rio Grande, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Point Pleasant, Gallipolis, Pomeroy, Rio Grande, Rutland, Mason,
Middleport, Henderson, Vinton, Cheshire, Adamsville, Lakin, Salem
Center, and Kyger.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

To report severe weather, contact your nearest law enforcement
agency. They will relay your report to the National Weather Service
office in Charleston West Virginia.</instruction>
